      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 146: Foreground restoration is gated on the current push setting/token. If accounts were already deactivated in the background and push is disabled or the token is cleared before the app is started again, this skips restoration and can leave those accounts inactive indefinitely. Since restoreProxyAccountsAfterBackground() only restores the recorded background-deactivated set, it is safe to call whenever transitioning from 0 started activities. Suggested fix:\n```suggestion\nif (startedActivityCount++ \u003d\u003d 0) {\n    Log.d(TAG, \"App came to foreground — reactivating accounts\")\n    mAccountService.restoreProxyAccountsAfterBackground()\n}\n```",
      "revId": "a96a9272e7fab868d85e4e7d54bff5d54b2d4e90",
